    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Phyllorkis aurea are skin conditions such as eczema, which is characterized by inflammation and redness of the skin. This plant is also effective in treating respiratory issues like bronchitis, a condition that causes inflammation of the lining of the bronchial tubes. Furthermore, Phyllorkis aurea has been used to alleviate pain and inflammation associated with arthritis, a condition that affects the joints and causes stiffness and swelling. In addition, the plant has been used to treat digestive issues such as constipation, a condition characterized by infrequent bowel movements. Phyllorkis aurea has also been used to lower blood pressure and alleviate symptoms of hypertension in individuals with this condition.",
