    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Phyllorkis aurea are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, and antifungal. Antimicrobial properties of this plant help prevent infections by inhibiting the growth of microorganisms, particularly in wound healing and skin conditions. Antioxidant properties, primarily attributed to flavonoids and phenolic acids, contribute to the plant's ability to scavenge free radicals and protect against cell damage. The antifungal properties of Phyllorkis aurea are crucial in treating fungal infections and diseases, such as athlete's foot and ringworm, thanks to the presence of volatile oils like geraniol and linalool. Anti-inflammatory properties, mediated by saponins and other bioactive compounds, help reduce inflammation and alleviate conditions like arthritis and eczema.",
