    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Phyllorkis aurea are iridoids such as aucubin and harpagoside which have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and scavenging free radicals. The flavonoids kaempferol and quercetin present in Phyllorkis aurea have also been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities through the suppression of pro-inflammatory cytokines and the protection of cells from oxidative damage. Additionally, the plant contains phenolic acids like caffeic acid and ferulic acid which have been reported to display antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects by disrupting the cell membrane of microorganisms and inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory mediators. The iridoid glycosides in Phyllorkis aurea have also been demonstrated to exhibit cardiotonic and diuretic activities by increasing the force of cardiac contractions and promoting the excretion of water and electrolytes. These healing constituents contribute to the medicinal properties of Phyllorkis aurea.",
