    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Phyllorkis aurea include tincture, which involves soaking the plant in a solvent to create a concentrated liquid extract, useful for its medicinal properties. Herbal tea or infusion involves steeping the plant in hot water to create a liquid for consumption, often used for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects. A salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant in a carrier oil and mixing with a wax, providing localized relief from skin irritations. Infused oil is prepared by steeping the plant in a carrier oil, often used for its antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties in skin treatments. These preparations are based on the plant's known constituents, including flavonoids and phenolic acids, which have been demonstrated to possess antimicrobial and antioxidant activities.",
