    "what_description": "Phyllorkis aurea is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It is a terrestrial orchid with a sympodial growth habit, producing a short stem with a few leaves. The plant has ovate to elliptic leaves, 10-20 cm long, with a leathery texture and a green color. The inflorescence is a raceme, 15-30 cm long, bearing 2-5 yellow flowers with a greenish-yellow labellum. The flowers have a 3-lobed labellum and a sepals and petals with a similar shape and size.",
    "uses": "Phyllorkis aurea is known for its use in traditional medicine, particularly in Asia. It is reported to have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may contribute to its medicinal applications. The plant's extracts have been studied for their potential in treating various health conditions, including wounds and infections. However, further research is needed to fully understand its therapeutic effects and safety. More studies are necessary to confirm its efficacy in treating specific health issues.",
    "taxonomy": "Phyllorkis aurea is a member of the family Orchidaceae. This family is one of the largest and most diverse groups of flowering plants, commonly known as orchids. The Orchidaceae family is further divided into several subfamilies, and Phyllorkis aurea is placed within the subfamily Orchidoideae. The Orchidoideae subfamily is a large and complex group, comprising many genera and species of orchids. Phyllorkis aurea is a specific species within this subfamily.",
    "benefits": "Phyllorkis aurea is a plant that has been traditionally used in various cultures for its medicinal properties. Studies on Phyllorkis aurea have shown potential in providing antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial benefits. The plant may also have immunomodulatory effects, which could help in boosting the body's immune system. Additionally, Phyllorkis aurea may have antiviral properties that could aid in fighting against certain viral infections. However, more research is needed to confirm its efficacy and optimal usage as a medicinal plant.",
    "parts": "Phyllorkis aurea contains rhizomes, which are traditionally used in herbal medicine. These rhizomes are valued for their potential anti-inflammatory properties and are used to treat various ailments. The rhizomes are often dried and processed into a powder or decoction. The medicinal properties of Phyllorkis aurea are attributed to the presence of certain bioactive compounds, which have been studied for their potential health benefits. Further research is needed to fully understand the medicinal properties and potential uses of Phyllorkis aurea.",
    "intro": "Phyllorkis aurea, also known as Golden Orchid, is a plant species within the Orchidaceae family, native to the tropical forests of Southeast Asia. The health benefits of Phyllorkis aurea include its potential anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antiviral properties, which can aid in the treatment of various diseases and injuries. The bioactive constituents of this plant include flavonoids, alkaloids, and saponins, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. The most common herbal preparations made with Phyllorkis aurea include teas, infusions, and tinctures, which are often used to relieve respiratory issues, fever, and skin conditions."
